- .lower() = all letters are lower case
- .upper() = all letters are upper case
- .title() = capital letter for the first letter of every word
- .capitalize() = capital letter for the first letter of only the first word
- .strip() = removes spaces at either side of the message

message = "Hello world".lower()
message = "hello world".upper()
message = "hello world".title()
message = "hello world".capitalize()
message = " hello world ".strip()

---

You can chain these functions together.

message = " hello world ".strip().capitalize() # Display Hello world
messge = " hello world".capitalize().strip() # Display hello world

Note: if you don't use strip() before capitalize() in this example, it won't capitalize the 'h' as the first key is a space
